The paper deals with the problem of learning ontologies, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of oracles and the analysis of conditions for query inseparability suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of queries also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy concerns related to the learning process, which could fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
